HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 204
BY REPRESENTATIVE DICKERSON
SPECIAL DAY/WEEK/MONTH: Designates April 28, 2026, as Domestic Violence
Prevention Advocacy Day in Louisiana
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To designate Tuesday, April 28, 2026, as Domestic Violence Prevention Advocacy Day in
3 the state of Louisiana.
4 WHEREAS, the members of the House of Representatives of the Legislature of
5 Louisiana recognize the need to address domestic violence; and
6 WHEREAS, domestic violence is a serious crime that affects people of all races,
7 ages, gender, and income levels; and
8 WHEREAS, domestic violence is widespread and affects thousands of Louisiana
9 families each year; and
10 WHEREAS, the act of domestic violence violates an individual's privacy, dignity,
11 security, and humanity due to the systematic use of physical, emotional, sexual,
12 psychological, and economic abuse; and
13 WHEREAS, domestic violence victims deserve access to safety, resources, and legal
14 protections; and
15 WHEREAS, The Louisiana Coalition Against Domestic Violence is the federally
16 designated statewide coalition of shelters, non-residential programs, and individuals working
17 to end domestic violence in Louisiana; and
18 WHEREAS, on April 28, 2026, the Louisiana Coalition Against Domestic Violence
19 will host its annual day at the state capitol with a display in Memorial Hall; and
20 WHEREAS, Domestic Violence Prevention Advocacy Day at the state capitol
21 provides an opportunity for citizens of Louisiana to learn more about preventing domestic
